# Bank Marketing SVM Classification

Comparing SVM kernels on the UCI Bank Marketing dataset to predict 
whether a customer will subscribe to a term deposit (binary classification).

## Key Result
Improved minority class (Yes) recall from 25% to 43% using class_weight balancing,
without generating synthetic data.

## Models Compared
- Linear SVM
- RBF SVM (best: C=10, gamma='scale')
- Polynomial SVM (degree=3)

## Dataset
UCI Bank Marketing — ~41,000 rows, 52 features after encoding
Class imbalance: ~88% No / ~12% Yes

## Key Findings
- RBF kernel outperformed linear and polynomial on minority class metrics
- class_weight='balanced' preferred over SMOTE — mathematically equivalent
  for SVM and avoids synthetic data artefacts
- Optimal C=0.01 for linear SVM, lower than default, indicating wider margin
  improves generalisation on this dataset

## Tech
Python, scikit-learn, pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn
